Package de.espirit.firstspirit.server.mediamanagement.exif

Interface ExifTags.Panasonic

  • Enclosing interface:
    ExifTags
    public static interface ExifTags.Panasonic
    Definition of specialized Panasonic Exif tags.

    For further descriptions, tags see http://www.exif.org/Exif2-2.PDF or the manufacturer definitions.

    Since:
    5.0.100

      static int TAG_FACE_DETECTION_INFO

      Integer (16Bit) Indexes:
      0 Number Face Positions (maybe less than Faces Detected)
      1-4 Face Position 1
      5-8 Face Position 2
      and so on

      The four Integers are interpreted as follows:
      (XYWH) X,Y Center of Face, (W,H) Width and Height
      All values are in respect to double the size of the thumbnail image
      static int TAG_FACE_RECOGNITION_INFO
      Byte Indexes:
      0 Int (2 Byte) Number of Recognized Faces
      4 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 1 Name
      24 4 Int (8 Byte) Recognized Face 1 Position (Same Format as Face Detection)
      32 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 1 Age
      52 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 2 Name
      72 4 Int (8 Byte) Recognized Face 2 Position (Same Format as Face Detection)
      80 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 2 Age

      And so on

      The four Integers are interpreted as follows:
      (XYWH) X,Y Center of Face, (W,H) Width and Height
      All values are in respect to double the size of the thumbnail image

      • TAG_AF_AREA_MODE

        static final int TAG_AF_AREA_MODE

        2 bytes
        (DMC-FZ10)
        '0 1' = Spot Mode On
        '0 16' = Spot Mode Off
        '(other models)
        16 = Normal?
        '0 1' = 9-area
        '0 16' = 3-area (high speed)
        '1 0' = Spot Focusing
        '1 1' = 5-area
        '16 0' = 1-area
        '16 16' = 1-area (high speed)
        '32 0' = Auto or Face Detect
        '32 1' = 3-area (left)?
        '32 2' = 3-area (center)?
        '32 3' = 3-area (right)?
        '64 0' = Face Detect

        For further descriptions, tags see http://www.exif.org/Exif2-2.PDF or the manufacturer definitions.

        Since:
        5.0.100
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • TAG_FACE_DETECTION_INFO

        static final int TAG_FACE_DETECTION_INFO

        Integer (16Bit) Indexes:
        0 Number Face Positions (maybe less than Faces Detected)
        1-4 Face Position 1
        5-8 Face Position 2
        and so on

        The four Integers are interpreted as follows:
        (XYWH) X,Y Center of Face, (W,H) Width and Height
        All values are in respect to double the size of the thumbnail image

        For further descriptions, tags see http://www.exif.org/Exif2-2.PDF or the manufacturer definitions.

        Since:
        5.0.100
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • TAG_FACE_RECOGNITION_INFO

        static final int TAG_FACE_RECOGNITION_INFO
        Byte Indexes:
        0 Int (2 Byte) Number of Recognized Faces
        4 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 1 Name
        24 4 Int (8 Byte) Recognized Face 1 Position (Same Format as Face Detection)
        32 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 1 Age
        52 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 2 Name
        72 4 Int (8 Byte) Recognized Face 2 Position (Same Format as Face Detection)
        80 String(20 Byte) Recognized Face 2 Age

        And so on

        The four Integers are interpreted as follows:
        (XYWH) X,Y Center of Face, (W,H) Width and Height
        All values are in respect to double the size of the thumbnail image

        For further descriptions, tags see http://www.exif.org/Exif2-2.PDF or the manufacturer definitions.

        Since:
        5.0.100
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
